	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Zelex wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Thats pretty awesome and it even works in my emulator too.</div>
<br />It's a clever CHR bankswitching trick. The game has CHR data for a number of horizontal patterns with perspective, and different patterns can be displayed in a single frame through bankswitching. Animation is achieved by moving the bankswitching spots every frame. Unfortunately, this trick can't be used for rotations.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


